  "instructions": [
    "1. Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "2. Roll out puff pastry and place on a baking sheet.",
    "3. In a large pan, caramelize onions over medium heat.",
    "4. Add garlic, melted butter, mellow cheese, Gruyère cheese, chives, salt, and pepper.",
    "5. Spread onion mixture over pastry, leaving a border.",
    "6. Fold pastry edges over filling and brush with egg wash.",
    "7. Bake for 25-30 minutes or until golden brown.",
    "8. Top with terrine, if using, and return to oven for 5 minutes.",
    "9. Let cool before serving."
  ],
